$ Avaloq: object relation

An object relation links two (or more?) objects.

A prominent example of such a relation is between a BP and his/her container(s).
Another is: asset and its trading place.

Relations have a type and a subtype.

{ Tables

  • code_obj_rel_type
  • code_obj_rel_sub_type

}
{ DDIC

  The `obj` → Companies-Products/Avaloq/development/DDIC[DDIC] provides the following methods
  to get relation info:
    • `rel_id`
    • `rel_item`
    • `rel_prio`
    • `rel_obj_list`
    • `rel_list`

}
